This looks almost ready to go. I've left some comments.

This looks good to me! The one issue I see is around naming. Edit: ignore my last comment -- I looked more closely and now understand what is being done here. IMO the property of a valuation being rank one is actually a `Prop` (some property about the type of convex subgroups of the value group), but now it's defined in a way that includes the data of the embedding into the reals. We can think about doing something about this later on.

Anyway, there is one minor comment below, then this PR should be good to go!

`rwa [Units.val_pow_eq_pow_val, _root_.map_pow]` would work here, but perhaps what you have is clearer and faster -- just not shorter.

```suggestion
```
`norm_def` sounds more like the name of a lemma saying that norm = something it's defined to be. Is there a reason that this isn't just called `norm`?
I can rename it to `norm`.
I feel like we can do a bit better with the name of this: e.g. `NNReal.exists_lt_of_strictMono` (and similar comment for the theorem below).

```suggestion
         haveI : Nontrivial  := (nontrivial_iff_exists_ne (1 : )).mpr
```
(it's a Prop)
These lines look very similar to 118-123, which I think are proving the other direction. Can they be factored out and can you prove both directions at once, or is this more trouble than it's worth?
Yes, each of these blocks proves one of the inclusions. I don't see a quick way of unifying the proofs.
this `letI` could also be made into a `haveI`.
